===Adjective===
{{en-adj-er-y|snazz|y}}

#(''informal'') Elegantly dressed.
#(''informal'') That works in a clever manner.
#:''This new mobile phone is really snazzy - you can download videos to it.''

====Synonyms====
*(''elegantly dressed''): [[dapper]], [[elegant]], [[smart]]
*(''that works in a clever manner''): [[cool]] (''informal''), [[nifty]] (''informal''), [[smart]]

====Antonyms====
*(''elegantly dressed''): [[inelegant]], [[scruffy]], [[sloppy]]
*(''that works in a clever manner''): [[crap]] (''coarse slang''), [[duff]], [[lame]] (''informal, especially US''), [[naff]] (''informal''), [[rubbish]] (''informal'')

